"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-16-svl-golden-ticket-winner-kerriane-mcbeans-paris-2024-dream-becomes-reality\", \"text\": \"Kerriane McBean, the lucky winner of Supreme Ventures Limited's (SVL) Golden Ticket promotion, lived the dream as she enjoyed an all-expense-paid trip to Paris 2024. Accompanied by her mother, Opal Swaby, McBean relished every moment of what was a truly once-in-a-lifetime experience.  The trip, which was organised and sponsored by Supreme Ventures, gave McBean and her mother the opportunity to immerse themselves in the excitement of the Olympic Games, where they were able to cheer on the athletes and even meet some of them in person. In addition to the thrilling sports events, McBean fulfilled a lifelong dream by visiting the iconic Eiffel Tower, a moment she described as \\\"surreal and everything she thought it would be\\\".  The pair also explored the stunning Palais Versailles, further enriching their Parisian adventure.  Reflecting on her incredible journey, McBean shared her gratitude, saying, \\\"This trip has been everything I ever imagined and more. Seeing the Eiffel Tower in person and walking through the halls of Versailles was a dream come true. I am so grateful to Supreme Ventures for making this possible and for treating us like royalty every step of the way.\\\"  Chloleen Daley-Muschett, corporate communications and PR manager at Supreme Ventures Limited, expressed her delight in being part of this special experience, stating, \\\"At SVL, we are committed to creating extraordinary experiences for our customers. It has been an absolute pleasure to watch Kerriane and her mother enjoy Paris and the Olympic Games. This Golden Ticket initiative embodies our dedication to rewarding our loyal customers in truly unique and memorable ways.\\\"  McBean's journey in Paris is a shining example of SVL's commitment to providing exceptional rewards and experiences for its customers. The company remains dedicated to creating opportunities that bring joy and unforgettable moments to the Jamaican community.          HOUSE RULES\"}"